    "Body": " Mergers & Acquisitions Specialist IBM - 3.9 United States Apply Now Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $95,000 - $130,000 a year2 days ago Benefits 401(k) Full Job Description Introduction This job role includes executing acquisitions, divestitures and investments on behalf of IBM clients to meet strategic goals of their organization. The responsibilities in this role focus on all elements of a transaction including but not limited to: project management, due diligence, presentations to senior executives, integration planning, Day 1 and Day 2 readiness planning and delivery, and post-transaction tracking. This job could range from phase 0 discovery through to long-term program leadership for large complex projects depending on skill level. Frequent interaction with IBM and client senior management is required along with the appropriate communication skills to address this level of executive inside IBM and externally. Broad knowledge of IBM and ability to manage external relationships are also key to superior performance in this role. Your Role and Responsibilities This job role is responsible for the development of the acquisition or divestiture IT and business alignment working in conjunction with the client and IBM SMEs to execute their business strategy and transformation opportunities. Extensive travel, both domestic and international, is often involved as the role will participate in on-site workshops and delivery co-located with the client, in their geos of operation. This role will work closely with Industry teams, Account teams, and IBM Services capabilities to ensure a holistic client solution is developed and delivered with the lens of M&A needs, constraints, and options for transaction value acceleration. It reports into the Cloud Advisory CoC globally and will work with other CoC capabilities to bring broad IBM technical capabilities to the broadest reach of client problems and needs for M&A driven modernization and change. Required Technical and Professional Expertise Proficiency with Excel, Word, PowerPoint, and MS Project Sales engagement and RFP/sales messaging Financial statement and business case synthesis Communication capabilities at the executive level IBM solutioning and deal shaping of 5+ yrs Client-facing program delivery leadership Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise Management experience of extended multi-geo teams Business and IT alignment experience Financial or other highly quantitative background M&A experience on acquisitions, divestitures, and JVs About Business Unit IBM Services is a team of business, strategy and technology consultants that design, build, and run foundational systems and services that is the backbone of the world's economy. IBM Services partners with the world's leading companies in over 170 countries to build smarter businesses by reimagining and reinventing through technology, with its outcome-focused methodologies, industry-leading portfolio and world class research and operations expertise leading to results-driven innovation and enduring excellence. Your Life @ IBM What matters to you when you\u2019re looking for your next career challenge? Maybe you want to get involved in work that really changes the world? What about somewhere with incredible and diverse career and development opportunities \u2013 where you can truly discover your passion? Are you looking for a culture of openness, collaboration and trust \u2013 where everyone has a voice? What about all of these? If so, then IBM could be your next career challenge. Join us, not to do something better, but to attempt things you never thought possible. Impact. Inclusion. Infinite Experiences. Do your best work ever. About IBM IBM\u2019s greatest invention is the IBMer. We believe that progress is made through progressive thinking, progressive leadership, progressive policy and progressive action. IBMers believe that the application of intelligence, reason and science can improve business, society and the human condition. Restlessly reinventing since 1911, we are the largest technology and consulting employer in the world, with more than 380,000 IBMers serving clients in 170 countries. Location Statement For additional information about location requirements, please discuss with the recruiter following submission of your application. Being You @ IBM IBM is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. IBM is also committed to compliance with all fair employment practices regarding citizenship and immigration status. "
